# Visualize sales distribution
ggplot(walmart_data, aes(x = Weekly_Sales)) + 
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 1000, fill = "skyblue", color = "black") +
  labs(title = "Distribution of Sales", x = "Weekly_Sales", y = "Frequency")

# Explore sales trends over time
ggplot(walmart_data, aes(x = Date, y = Weekly_Sales)) + 
  geom_line(color = "blue") +
  labs(title = "Sales Trend Over Time", x = "Date", y = "Weekly_Sales")

## Handling missing values (if any)
# Check for missing values
colSums(is.na(walmart_data))
##        Store         Date Weekly_Sales Holiday_Flag  Temperature   Fuel_Price

## Time Series Analysis with Arima 
# Convert data to time series
walmart_ts <- ts(walmart_data$Weekly_Sales, frequency = 52)
# Fit ARIMA model
arima_model <- auto.arima(walmart_ts)
# Forecast future sales
sales_forecast <- forecast(arima_model, h = 10)
# Visualize forecasted sales
plot(sales_forecast, main = "Forecasted Sales")

## Model Evaluation
# Calculate Mean Absolute Error (MAE)
mae <- mean(abs(fitted(arima_model) - walmart_ts))
mae
## [1] 80894.65
# Calculate Mean Squared Error (MSE)
mse <- mean((fitted(arima_model) - walmart_ts)^2)
# Print evaluation metrics
print(paste("MAE:", mae))
## [1] "MAE: 80894.6505238254"
print(paste("MSE:", mse))
## [1] "MSE: 22604514530.6844"
